Many give up at this stage. Others write apologies to their former bosses and request to return to employment.Quote Tweet CK Japheth @CKJapheth  ¬∑ Sep 9, 2020 The 1,000 day rule. In short, you must be willing to do worse than you used to or at your job for 1000 days ‚Äì about 3 years passing through the trough of sorrow, uncertainty, trial & error, wins & failures before you reach a reasonably comfortable & stable income level. 7/ Show this thread
